article.linkText: Vinson scores 17, Northern Kentucky downs Eastern Kentucky 85-75
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- — Sam Vinson scored 17 points as Northern Kentucky beat Eastern Kentucky 85-75 on Sunday night. Vinson had seven rebounds for the Norse (7-5). Jeramiah Israel scored 15 points and added five rebounds. Trey Robinson finished with 14 points, while adding eight rebounds and three steals. The Colonels (4-6) were led by Isaiah Cozart, who recorded 24 points, 13 rebounds and five blocks. John Ukomadu added 15 points and seven rebounds for Eastern Kentucky. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
